<li style="-webkit-text-size-adjust: none; color: #2D2B19; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; margin-top: 0; mso-line-height-rule: exactly; margin-bottom: 0;">RAND Europe's Mehdi Shiva explains how <a href="https://www.rand.org/pubs/commentary/2025/05/innovative-finance-in-public-health-promise-pitfalls.html??cutoff=true&amp;utm_source=AdaptiveMailer&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=7014N000001SnimQAC&amp;utm_term=00v4N00000X4BbbQAF&amp;org=1674&amp;lvl=100&amp;ite=297416&amp;lea=548321&amp;ctr=0&amp;par=1&amp;trk=a0wQK00000CZAOzYAP" style="-webkit-text-size-adjust: none; color: #4E4D8F; text-decoration: underline;">innovative financing tools</a> can help governments navigate economic uncertainty while meeting increasing public health needs.</li>
